            "updated_at": "2018-01-08T18:07:55Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "While I understand the reasoning behind this change, I think it is a bad idea. Everybody associates debug mode with the reloader and the debugger, since this is something that's been true for a very long time. The reality is that people are slowly starting to migrate from `app.run(debug=True)` to `FLASK_DEBUG=1`, while a large group of developers still don't understand what's wrong with `app.run()`, and I find myself explaining it to a lot of people.\r\n\r\nI'm against introducing another breaking change in the workflow."
        },
