            "created_at": "2018-01-08T19:03:11Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-08T19:03:11Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "After some discussion, we decided to leave the reloader tied to `FLASK_DEBUG` instead of moving it to `FLASK_ENV`. I think this will cause the least confusion.\r\n\r\nCurrently, the only thing that will happen if users stick with `FLASK_DEBUG=1` instead of `FLASK_ENV=development` is that they will get a warning about running the server in production. Ideally, users switch to `FLASK_ENV` and only use `FLASK_DEBUG` as an override."
        },
