            "created_at": "2018-01-08T19:08:14Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-08T19:08:14Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@mitsuhiko I think deprecating the `debug` argument in `app.run()` is a good idea.\r\n\r\n> The reason environments are important is that everything currently uses debug to indicate development mode which is a terrible idea once ngrok and other things are involved.\r\n\r\nI'm not against environments, but honestly I think they are unnecessary. What I do in my own development workflow is to never use `FLASK_DEBUG`, and I don't see a need to adopt `FLASK_ENV` either. If I want the reloader, I use `--reload`, and if I want the debugger I use `--debugger`. Better to be explicit. When I convince people to forget about \"debug mode\" and use what they need, confusion goes away."
        },
