            "created_at": "2018-01-08T19:51:38Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-08T19:51:38Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@miguelgrinberg the main reason the environments are useful is because right now a bunch of stuff breaks development wise if debug is disabled. In particular I cannot tell things like webpack to only run when debug is on. That would mean the debug mode is required for the dev stuff in webpack to run which is not great.\r\n\r\nSo I want to establish a common flag that indicates \"this is development\" without dangerous tools being forcefully enabled. The goal is to have `FLASK_ENV` mirror into `NODE_ENV` if flask launches a node thing."
        },
