            "created_at": "2018-01-08T22:16:59Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-08T22:19:03Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yeah, absolutely, I think `FLASK_ENV=production` is the right default.\r\n\r\nNot convinced about your argument for not setting `DEBUG` in configuration. I think the confusing part is to know what it does exactly to your application now that the reloader & debugger are not controlled by it, but I don't think it is confusing if you think of it as a flag that you can later check. The documentation for `DEBUG` and `TESTING` is very vague, still refers to \"debug\" and \"testing\" modes. If we explicitly describe what each of these flags do, then I think it would be a lot less confusing to users.\r\n  "
        },
