            "created_at": "2018-01-08T22:35:25Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-08T22:35:25Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@miguelgrinberg my thinking was also that `TESTING` would be largely replaced by a reasonable flask env value. Maybe that's not the right way to go about this but the issue with setting things like `DEBUG` in the config is that way too much stuff initializes too early. More importantly a lot of stuff that is debug related just can't access the config yet because it's not there.\r\n\r\nSo not sure if we can ever make `DEBUG` work well in the config unless we re-initialize things on config change."
