            "created_at": "2018-01-09T00:49:18Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-09T00:49:18Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> So not sure if we can ever make DEBUG work well in the config unless we re-initialize things on config change.\r\n\r\nRight, the reloader in particular would be very hard to control through something in `app.config`. I sort of stopped thinking about the debugger and the reloader as \"debug mode\" things, and instead consider them separate options that you can enable when you need them.\r\n\r\nWith this way of seeing things, the `FLASK_DEBUG=1` option enables, three things by default: the reloader, the debugger, and debug mode in the application. So setting debug mode in the application does not imply that you are using the debugger & reloader, just that `app.debug==True`. Not sure if I can convince you to look at things this way, but at least for me it clears most of the confusion around these options, and makes `DEBUG` perfectly safe to stay in the configuration."
        }
